10. Kd1
10. Be6 {In an early draft of this chapter I gave10...Bxd3!?11.cxd3Nxd3,which is not bad for Black but unnecessarily messy (White will often lose the queen but get a lot of material for it).Instead, after10...Be6White just has a clumsy position - the pieces are misplaced and he has lost the right to castle. There is also a threat of ...Nxa2, for instance11.Nf3?Nxa2!and White can only avoid the discovery ...Nc3+ with12.Rb1when12...Nxc1leaves Black with an extra pawn and the superior position.} 
