7. Bb3 {If at any time White plays Be2, we can just continue ...Nxd5 and enjoy the better pawn structure.} 
7. a5 {At this point7...g6is a good alternative, just finishing kingside development and only then continuing with ...a5-a4 and ...Na6-c7 etc. However, immediately pushing the queenside pawns is more fun.At this point we'll look at four possible continuations by White:8.Nf3,8.Nc3,8.a4and the main move8.a3.} 
8. a3 {The main move and the move which was seen in a few high level games, like a rapid game between Nigel Short and Anatoly Karpov. White prepares a square on a2 for his bishop to retreat to.} 
