9. O-O
10. Bxd7 {The last possible moment for this capture:10.O-O?Nc6!11.Bxc6Rb8!} 
10. Nbxd7
11. d4 {11.O-O?again allows11...Bxh2+!.} 
11. Nb6 {...Re8 is also possible, but I prefer this move because: 1) there are no good other squares for the d7-knight anyway, and 2) we can toy with the idea of trapping White's queen.} 
12. Qa6 {This is how White should continue, preventing Black from playing ...a6 and trapping White's queen.} 
