9. Nc6 {L'Ami's conclusion was: 'with an unclear game'. Let's unpack a bit what is happening here.White has an extra pawn on the d-file and some light-squared weaknesses. In particular there are ideas in this position of playing Nb4-d3+, which is very annoying for White.Also, White has some problems getting castled, as10.Nf3runs into10...Qe7+!.} 
10. Ne2
10. Nb4 {10...Rc8is also possible and likely transposes.} 
11. O-O {The only move.11.Qb5+?even loses after11...Qd712.Qxd7+Kxd7, as White is forced to play13.Kd1, but then13...Ng4has no good answer(14.Rf1Nxh2etc.).} 
11. Rc8
12. Qb5+ {Necessary. Otherwise ...Nc2 follows and White won't get enough compensation for the exchange.} 
12. Qd7
13. Qxd7+
13. Nxd7
14. Nbc3
14. Nd3 {The extra pawn is pretty meaningless in this position. A good scheme of development for Black is ...Bc5, ...N7e5 and short castling. Both d2 and f2 are good targets.} 
