8. exf4 {I think we should just take the bishop.8...Na5gets a higher score from the computer but I don't think it leads to pleasant positions for Black, as explained in the preceding informational line.} 
9. hxg4
9. Qe7+ {This is an important point. We don't go for the g4-pawn (at least not immediately), but first want to castle queenside as soon as possible.} 
10. Ne2 {The only real alternative to10.Kf1. However I feel that this misplaces the knight a bit.} 
10. O-O-O
11. Nd2 {11.g5?would be a mistake. First off, the pawn wasn't hanging yet, as ...Nxg4 is answered by Bf5+ as long as Black's king is on c8. But after11...Ne4the pawn will probably be lost next with ...Nxg5.} 
11. Kb8 {A mandatory move in these positions. We don't want to run into11. ..Nxg4??12.Bf5+.Now after11...Kb8the g4-pawn is actually hanging (e.g.12.O-O-O?Nxg4is just very good for Black).} 
12. g5 {Probably necessary now.} 
12. Ng4 {Play becomes very concrete.12...Ne4looks nice, for instance, but doesn't seem to lead to much after13.Bxe4!dxe414.Nxf4e315.Nf3!when White just has an extra pawn.After12...Ng4, Black has two threats. The obvious one is13.--Qxg5, the slightly less obvious (and more significant) one is13.--Nxf2!.} 
13. Bb5 {White needs to play energetically. Moves like13.Qc2and13.Rh3address the threat of ...Nxf2, but Black could answer13...Qxg5and ask White to demonstrate the compensation for the pawn.} 
13. Qc7 {I think this is the easiest answer, though13...Na5is definitely a good possibility too. With13...Qc7we simply protect the knight on c6 as well as the pawn on f4, and make space for the f8-bishop to be developed.After13...Qc7White has a wide variety of choices. The computer likes14.a4best, which is not at all an obvious move. I think it makes sense to prepare ...a6 with14...Ka8, when15.a5a616.Bd3g6leads to a hard to assess position. A materialistic try is14.Bxc6?!Qxc615.Nxf4Bd616.Nd3Rhe8+17.Kf1Qa6.White is up a pawn but has some problems to solve.Finally, the computer also gives the suggestion of going into an ending with14.Qa4Bd615.Bxc6Qxc616.Qxc6bxc6,but I think Black should be fine here. Note that the g4-knight is never in danger of being trapped, as Rh4 can always be answered by ...h5 and f3 with ...Ne3.} 
