10. Nd2 {This seems to be the most natural move.10.e6?!Nxg311.exf7+Qxf712.hxg3O-O-Odoesn't help White at all.10.Qxd5?!Rd811.Qe4Nxg312.hxg3Qd7sees White in big trouble, as13.Be2?runs into13...Qd1+!and mate.Perhaps10.Be2is objectively best, but at the very least Black can try10...Nxg311.hxg3Be6!followed by castling long, with fun play.} 
10. Nxg3
11. hxg3
11. O-O-O {Now we're finally ready to take on e5.} 
12. f4 {White might as well hold on to the pawn, as12.Ngf3Nxe513.Nxe5Qxe5+sees him lose the right to castle.} 
12. f6
13. exf6
13. gxf6 {Followed by moves like ...Bc5 and ...d4 with excellent compensation for the pawn.} 
