11. h6 {11...Nd7would be standard development, but because our queen loses contact with the d5-square, White can favorably break with12.d5!(12...Bxc3?13.dxe6!)11...Nbc612.d5exd513.Nxd5Nxd514.Bxd5is also a bit better for White, though Black's position is playable after14...Qf6.Instead of developing the b8-knight, we first take the time to prevent White from playing Bg5 altogether.} 
