9. e6 {Banzea considers9...Nf5, which is also a viable move, but after the pointed10.Ne1!Bxe211.Nxe2c512.c3cxd413.cxd4White keeps a pleasant space advantage. I also want to play ...c5 and exchange on d4, but prepare that with a move that we have to play anyway (...e6), while delaying ...Nf5 has its advantages as we will see.} 
