11. Nbc6
12. Qa4 {Now Black has many good moves, but simplest is} 
12. f4 {just pre-emptively opening the g6-bishop's diagonal. Next Black can consider ...a6 and ...b5 or perhaps ...Qc7 as the e5-pawn is, as usual, a weakness.} 
