9. c3 {If9.dxc5Nc610.Bf4e6it doesn't seem like White can keep his extra pawn.9.Nxh5?!is not a good idea due to9...Nf5when both d4 and h4 are weak.} 
9. Nc6
10. Be3
10. Ng4 {Another important idea. Here White struggles with how to answer a potential ...Nxe3. If fxe3, this weakens the g4-square a lot which can be exploited with ...Qg4. While if Qxe3, then ...g6 followed by ...Bh6 can be very annoying. There are also ideas of ...Rc8 followed by ...cxd4 and ...Nb4 in the position.} 
