14. Ng5 {This is the best move after 13... Kc8, but here the tactical details don't work out for White.} 
14. Nh6
15. Bh5
15. Be7 {This move doesn't work in the same position with 13...Kc8, but here it's a problem for White.At this point White should probably bail out with16.Bd1Rxa8when he is clearly worse.} 
