16. Qxd2+
17. Kxd2
17. Nbd7 {This is the type of ending where both sides can play for a win, in my opinion. White has a bit more space, but h5 is often a weakness. Generally Black will want to advance his pawns on the queenside, but which pawn advance is best depends on the circumstances.Here, if White plays18.b4, for instance, then18...a5seems a good answer, intending19.b5cxb5getting the d5-square, while otherwise we can open the a-file at the right moment. Meanwhile,18.a4a5would allow us to get hold of the b4-square.} 
18. Kc3
18. b5 {18...c5has been played a few times here, but it seems a small mistake to me, as after19.dxc5Nxc520.Rhe1the knight will get kicked out following b2-b4.} 
