19. bxc4
20. bxc4
20. c5 {This is an idea I wanted to show. Now20.dxc5Nxc5is a clearly superior version of 18...c5 earlier. The computer already wants White to sacrifice a pawn with20.d5exd521.Rhe1+Kf8at this point, though I question whether he has enough compensation.} 
