12. Nc6 {Black needs to keep developing. All the alternatives just suck.} 
13. Nxc5 {Of course this capture needs to be checked, but it seems to work out fairly well for Black.} 
13. Bxc5
14. dxc5
14. Qxd3
15. cxd3
15. O-O-O
16. Ke2
16. Rd5 {After several forcing moves Black regains the pawn with a good position. Before taking either c5 or h5, it's good to first develop the other rook to the d-file as well.} 
