16. Bxb4+
17. c3
17. Be7
18. O-O-O {White has a slight lead in development and better centralization. However, the position is quite open which favors the bishop, and if Black can get castled too he should be completely fine.} 
18. Qd5 {There are other moves too, but this seems easiest to me. Now19.c4?Rc8is very good for Black, so White should play something calm.} 
19. Kb1
19. O-O-O {With a good position. If White allows it, Black can consider playing ...f5 and ...Bf6 next.} 
