16. Kg8 {Now Black is threatening17.--Nxe5followed by ...Nxg4.} 
17. Rg1
17. Nxe5 {Anyway!} 
18. fxe5
18. Ne8 {Now h4 is hanging while the knight will help with the defense of the kingside via g7.} 
19. g5 {Perhaps19.O-O-Ois stronger, but then Black can just take19...Bxh4.} 
19. hxg5 {Next the knight will come to f5. Our king can (temporarily) hide on h8 if necessary. It might look a bit dodgy, but in the end we do have an extra piece.} 
