16. Nf5 {Now after most queen moves, ...Qg5+ usually gives Black very good play.} 
17. Qf2
17. Qg5+
18. Kb1
18. Qg4 {This is a key theme to remember. Black physically prevents White from playing g2-g4, and this way the knight is secured on f5.} 
