20. Qa1+ {Here Black has to repeat moves. If White wants, though, he can play on with21.Qb1Qxb1+22.Kxb1,entering an endgame. However, he does this at his own peril. Objectively it is equal, and in the 4 games that continued this way, Black scored 3 out of 4.} 
21. Kc2
21. Qa4+ {Due to the skewer White has to go back with22.Kc1when22...Qa1+follows, etc.} 
