 {But White doesn't have to transpose at all, as this is doing Black a service. After 5... Nf6 I fail to see how Black equalizes in case of} 6. O-O {Now6...e6would be an admission of failure, keeping the c8-bishop boxed in, while both6...Bd7and6...Bf5are answered by7.c4!with some initiative for White.} 
6. Bg4 {remains, but} 
7. h3 {is awkward. Now7...Bxf3just gives up the bishop pair, while} 
7. Bh5
8. g4
8. Bg6
9. Ne5 {followed by h4-h5 is perhaps even worse (this chase of the light-squared bishop is a typical motif, and it works even while White has already castled kingside).} 
