[Result "*"]

1. e4
1. c6
2. Nf3
2. d5
3. exd5
3. cxd5
4. Ne5 {The idea is to frustrate Black's development and force us to give up the bishop pair, as we will see.} 
4. Nc6
5. Bb5 {This is an alternate move order that should amount to the same thing.} 
5. Bd7
6. Nxd7
6. Qxd7 {Now White can't really go without the move d4 anyway, hence a transposition is very likely.} 
7. d4 {Now 7... e6 transposes. L'Ami offers a different line, however:} 
