12. Nf3 {White prevents ...e5 directly.} 
12. Ne4 {The issue with Nf3 is, as usual, that it allows for ...Ne4.} 
13. Ng5 {Gawain's recommendation, after which he analyses both13...Nxg514.Bxg5e5, which should be slightly better for White, and13...f5?!14.Nh3!when, following f2-f3, White gets a large positional advantage.} 
13. Nf6 {But what about just retreating? The white knight isn't doing much on g5 and this invites a move repetition with14.Nf3Ne4. I don't really see what else White can do.} 
14. g3 {Perhaps this move keeps the game going, bolstering the kingside in advance of an impending ...e5.} 
14. h6 {I suggest we simply kick the knight and play ...Ne4 again.} 
15. Nf3
15. Ne4
16. Ne5
16. Qc7 {I don't really see what White is doing, while we intend to clarify the situation with ...a6 next.} 
